This paper discusses a system that provides a censorship-resistant distributed service for the exchange of information over the Internet using web annotations. The paper focuses on the use of blockchain and IPFS, which are commonly used in the areas of computer security (cs.CR), distributed computing (cs.DC), digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and social and information networks (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DL, cs.IR, and cs.SI, in that order.
